Class IdentTable

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--de.cocolab.reuse.IdentTable
public class IdentTable
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

Identifier tables.

Each instance of this class maintains a table of Ident objects, such that given any particular string value, the same Ident object is always returned.

Each Ident is also numbered starting from 1 (zero being used to represent no identifier). This may be used as an index into a symbol table.

Method Detail

makeIdentCode

public int makeIdentCode(java.lang.String s)
Create an identifier from a given String, returning an int code.

The number returned is suitable for use as an index into a symbol table. It is the same value as you would obtain by 

     int code;
     Ident id;
     id = ids.makeIdent("name");
     code = id.value;

This interface is provided for use where symbol table lookups are frequent, and the removal of the overhead involved in saying symbolTable[id.value] instead of symbolTable[code] is more important than the loss in clarity and type safety.

length

public int length()
Return length of the used part of the identifier table. This can be used to create an array to be indexed with the identifier code. Index zero of the array would not normally be used as it corresponds to noIdent.

Returns:
Number of identifiers stored including 'no identifier'.
